{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"51fca8b0-45fc-4988-86fc-eaf72fe7f913","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet restore` to pull updated packages, then `dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check for any NuGet packages (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) that need their major version bumped to 11.x as well.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e417c9df-ccdd-4a3c-a54f-84fa43e18284","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward knowledge question — I'll provide a concise answer covering the three areas they mentioned.","outputTokens":263,"requestId":"9847:7AD2E:22F5BA:2BC23B:69F5562F"},"id":"d011b968-ed1f-4832-8d23-b92a2d96bbf3","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:41:09.470Z","parentId":"e050d45e-379d-40b5-b285-feb4c2fb3132"}
